      "file": "src/app/okta.config.ts",
      "description": "## Configure Codespace visibility\n\nWe use the configuration values you added to initialize Okta. Notice the request includes scopes for reading Okta Users API.\n\nLet's start the app. Open a new terminal window by navigating to the **TERMINAL** tab and selecting the ➕ (plus) icon. Run the command `npm start` in the new terminal.\n\nThe app needs to be visible to Okta to complete the sign-in process:\n1. Open the **PORTS** panel within this window and find the app running on port 4200.\n2. Right click on the app and select **Port visibility** > **Public**.\n3. Click the 🌐 (web) icon to open your app in a new browser tab.\n\nYou should see the SPA DPoP Lab site running from the Codespace. If you see a warning from GitHub about accessing a development port in a codespace, select the **Continue** button.\n\nSign in using the credentials provided for your Okta training org. Next up - tokens!",
